# Satisfactory server (this repo)

Fork-style image and scripts derived from [indifferentbroccoli/satisfactory-server-docker](https://github.com/indifferentbroccoli/satisfactory-server-docker). Prefer matching upstream behavior when fixing bugs; document DataKnife-specific changes in commit messages.

## Authoritative hosting docs

- [Indifferent Broccolipedia](https://wiki.indifferentbroccoli.com) — game server hosting guides (includes [Satisfactory](https://wiki.indifferentbroccoli.com/Satisfactory)).
- Use the wiki for `.env` semantics, ports, and operational troubleshooting alongside this repo’s `README.md` and `.env.example`.

## Layout

- `scripts/` — entrypoint (`init.sh`, `start.sh`), SteamCMD install, INI generation from templates.
- `Dockerfile` — `cm2network/steamcmd` base; game files under `/satisfactory`, configs from env.
- `deploy/` — Kustomize: `deploy/kustomization.yaml` includes `base` (`deploy/base/`). Trial sizing + `game-servers` namespace: `kubectl apply -k deploy/overlays/min-spec/` (expects `harbor-registry-secret` in that namespace). Default: `kubectl apply -k deploy/`.
- `.github/actions/verify-game-server/` — shared CI: Shellcheck, Hadolint (threshold: **error**), Markdownlint, Yamllint, `kubectl kustomize` compile.

## Kubernetes

- Create a ConfigMap from your real env (see `.env.example`), e.g. `satisfactory-server-env`, referenced by the Deployment.
- Ensure cluster pull secrets for Harbor if the registry is private.

## GitLab mirror and CI

See `docs/GITLAB_MIRROR.md`. GitHub Actions mirrors `main` to GitLab; GitLab CI builds and pushes to Harbor using `HARBOR_*` variables.
